	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Balkamp</b><br /><i>The +hp component is going to make every MT want it cast on them, period. The "vision" of this spell is FA-like &amp; if that's the case, BEEF it UP! Castable discipline? that's fine, but discs don't take buff slots, this will. Figure out some way to make it stack on/with wunshi without overwriting it. ie occupies the same buff slot, but when it fades, wunshi re-appears.<br />
<br />
MT's in my guild are already clicking off sense, declining (rightfully so) might, &amp; turning down charisma (DI). All to save precious buff slots even the 5 extra they bought via aa. I don't want another buff, that takes another seperate slot that the MT WILL WANT despite its crap duration.<br />
<br />
This is not my only problem with this spell, just one of them.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Your MT's are probably clicking off sense because they are tanking with evasive, which will overwrite sense, or because they think its agility. Generally speaking if you have to make choices about buffs, you pick hp buffs over mitigation/avoidance buffs since they deal with damage spikes better, so, if they have to lose a buff, it probably would be sense. And just remember, given a choice and provided that it can be maintained, most (well, lets say all) MTs would choose a 1500hp buff over a 680 one (wunshi) or a 412hp one (BBB). MT's dont need might since their role isnt dps, and raid MT's with decent equipment generally have good CHA, so casting reverance on them is just an annoyance. Don't do it unless they ask you to. Same deal with might. The chances that they would intentionally click off panther are about zero.</p>
	
	
	
