	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Well, if you have enough shaman it will be a required rotation. There might be the odd individual that would refuse to cast the spell, and if they are in a guild that tolerates carrying dead weight, then that might be ok. Most proper raiding guilds will probably insist though, and I think that most shaman will do the right thing, after all, they probably want to win encounters, particularly challenging ones. And in any case, even with less than optimal numbers, having periods of elevated hp would still have a significant impact on reducing risk. For example, if you only have one shaman, timing the spell to land just before the MTs discs fade would be usefull.<br />
<br />
The point is, properly used, this spell could be a powerfull weapon in the raiders arsenal.</p>
	
	
	
