	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Considering I sometimes even forget to recast champion, which is a one minute refresh on the gem, and even gives me an icon for which to time its duration, I don't see how I could possibly keep myself in any sort of rotation of this spell on the tank. Now I'll address this gem:<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Not all MTs are warriors, and not all warriors are MTs. I highly doubt that Frodlin thinks that the primary role of the MT is dps.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Your primary banner that you've been parading around in this thread is that every tank is going to want this spell for the 1500hp, yet the spell it self is contradictory. The HP component and its retardedly short duration gives the dilemma where encounters are going to be designed requiring the tank to have 1500 more HP, yet the crit component is surely better being cast on a DPS class.<br />
<br />
If you absolutely must keep this spell and its retarded limitations, remove the hit point component completely. I absolutely refuse to mire myself into some sort of rotation of anything. I have enough sh*t to be worrying about on most encounters already. If it is intended to be a "Discipline" as Rytan said, then make it purely DPS oriented, so that I can hand it out at my leisure.<br />
<br />
Tugela simply doesn't understand certain things, having not played in a raid enviornment on his shaman. A good example would be Quarm in time for instance. Here's the situation:<br />
<br />
1) 3800 max hit. a quad for full without defensive can one round the tank.<br />
2) Tons of AEs, need to keep people cured.<br />
3) Annoyingly resistant, need to alternate TA/Nihil to slow usually.<br />
4) Need to heal group in addition to slowing and curing.<br />
<br />
On quarm, here's what my spell gems look like:<br />
<br />
1) Disinfecting Aura<br />
2) Blood of Nadox<br />
3) Serenity<br />
4) Malos<br />
5) Nihil<br />
6) RGC<br />
7) Yoppa's<br />
8) Pained Memory<br />
9) Abolish Disease (that slow is the devil, gotta get it in one shot.)<br />
<br />
My guild got hit hard by burnout/eq2/wow, and a lot of our new recruits have horrible resists. To top it off, We've had 1-2 bards on for time the last couple weeks, so getting resists on Quarm is an issue sometimes. I usually split the curing up with 1 other shaman, or rarely two. During the fight, between trying to slow after each head explodes, plus cure my group or anyone that sends me tells, plus heal my group, plus keep myself alive, there is absolutely no time for me to worry about my turn to refresh this spell on anyone. Even if I had a second where I could toss it on someone, I can't because I don't have a spell gem to waste on it.<br />
<br />
Once again, I'm strongly suggesting they make this an AA ability, and remove the HP component so that no MT would want it. Have it decrease the user's mana if you must.<br />
<br />
You can steal my spell gems when you pry them from my cold dead hands.</p>
	
	
	
