	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />If I wanted to be in a lousy rotation, I would play a cleric. Short duration buffs are the devil.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Amen.<br />
<br />
Are they TRYING to take every ounce of fun out of the class? Thus far, they're succeeding. <br />
<br />
There's already a dry run of raiding Shaman on my server, between transfers, retirees, and people just quitting the game or the class. Short Duration buffs are bad. They're a stigma on this class, and give a lot of overworked Shaman even more to do.<br />
<br />
This class is not an occupation. I don't want to have to constantly refresh short duration buffs, because of someone short-sightedness in developing spells for this class. I've got enough on my plate.<br />
<br />
Honestly, this just goes back to the whole, "Who let someone design these spells, why do they think this way, and what do I do with them after I stuff them in my trunk?" line of reasoning.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><div align="center">=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=<br />
