	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I think I am starting to look through this. The spell looks a lot like something to give to a class to increase their group desirability. Something very simple, an HP buff with a short duration as to not be able to be cast by a bot or in PoK.<br />
<br />
This is definitely something every group would want a Shaman for. At the same time it's a horribly boring concept.<br />
<br />
I am sure we will see one or more spells along these lines for each class. Something unique a group will want them for, but very flat and uninspired. We'll see if that's the way to go for EQ in regards to balancing classes versus each other.<br />
<br />
To me it looks like this concept is taking precedence over adressing the top 10 class issues(isn't DoN release really close already?) and I am not sure I like that.<br />
<br />
Imo, SoE would be best off delaying the DoN release a few months. Adress the class issues, rebalance DPS and healing in general for all classes and then start designing these unique spells to increase everyone's group desirability in that order. <br />
<br />
3 months of beta testing(yes, make it part of the DoN beta) should be good enough, I'd say.</p>
	
	
	
