<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>veeshanMurtak</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Luminary<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2004<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Shamylamy</b><br /><i>I don't see the problem with casting this. We have usually between 2 to 7 shamans per raid nowadays, usually 5+, and that extra HP would really make the raid happier. I'm pretty sure they are going to have us keep this spell up on as many tanks in the rotation as possible. I don't think most shamans are going to have a choice on whether to keep this up or not, I bet it's going to be required.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>And that is part of why the spell is crap. If clerics got a spell that required them to type out "walla walla" every 20 seconds but made CH cost no time you bet it would be required on raids and a powerful ability in groups as well (which this piece of crap is not).<br />
<br />
That does not make it desirable, does not help the class, does not make it fun - it only makes it annoying and powerful. There is no need for that. You can not balance power with annoyance, so all spells, all abilities should be balanced by power and then have their annoyance minimized. Adding annoying powerful abilities only results in annoying one part of your playerbase and having the other part ignore something SOE spent precious development time on.<br />
<br />
If shamans for some odd reason need the ability to give the MT more HPs to balance the class but for equally odd reasons it would be overpowering to cast it on the entire raid just make it a 10 min refresh, 40 min duration. Of course with the recast time now gone it seems like that was never a balancing factor to begin with. Apparently we are to decide between giving someone +1500 HPs or casting a nuke or real heal. I think I would still be happier with the 10 min / 40 min  duration, even though that is an annoying spell too. Because I don't have to keep a list of people to rotate this on that way and also because I can get back to casting <b>real</b> heals during combat, which beats having rogue_no_192 having a prettier number in his inventory.<br />
<br />
Rytan, if you read this, would you mind telling us what this spell is supposed to do for us shaman and how you want us to use it (or rather, how you not want us to use it)? I am sure we can come up with a ton of good ideas. Currently it seems like a rather narrow spell that has a huge annoyance factor, and I am sure annoying customers is not what the spell was supposed to do.</p>
	
	
	
